  <locationDescription><![CDATA[<p>A multi-centre holiday lets you mix and match hotels, lengths of stay, and exciting activities to create your ideal trip. Enjoy everything from guided walks and outdoor adventures to relaxing lakeside days and tasty local cuisine.</p>
<p><strong>Explore Lake Como's hidden gems and blockbuster hotspots</strong></p>
<p>Want to get to know the real Lake Como? Then put on your walking boots and hit the trails above <a data-udi="umb://document/80beb49bbb7f416ba46131e7c79367b5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/80beb49bbb7f416ba46131e7c79367b5}" title="Menaggio">Menaggio</a>, <a data-udi="umb://document/d3611d3782e0494ead59e534458bcdd6" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d3611d3782e0494ead59e534458bcdd6}" title="Bellagio">Bellagio</a> and <a data-udi="umb://document/164b7f39f6d74033a2991f5799ebdfa7" href="/{localLink:umb://document/164b7f39f6d74033a2991f5799ebdfa7}" title="Lenno">Lenno</a>. Walking above and around the lake will open up an entire area of traditional farmland, mountain huts, sleepy old towns and historic churches, that you'd have never seen following the typical tourist trail. If glitz and glam are more up your street then there are also plenty of opportunities for star-spotting and scoping out famous villas. From George Clooney's old Lake Como pad to Lenno's Villa Balbianello, used in the James Bond and Star Wars franchises.</p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/7d421e04a79044babf8cafda30e31d4a" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7d421e04a79044babf8cafda30e31d4a}" title="Lake Como" class="c-btn c-btn--secondary c-btn c-btn--mid c-btn--secondary-hollow c-btn--wide u-text-center">Find Out More About Lake Como</a></p>
<p><strong>Hop between the Borromean islands and walk along the promenade in Lake Maggiore</strong></p>
<p>Get to know Lake Maggiore, while based in the relaxed lakeside towns of <a data-udi="umb://document/44b05c95e1264c56b51016621b99f80b" href="/{localLink:umb://document/44b05c95e1264c56b51016621b99f80b}" title="Stresa">Stresa</a> or <a data-udi="umb://document/40af41087b6c40cd950bbe672939b005" href="/{localLink:umb://document/40af41087b6c40cd950bbe672939b005}" title="Baveno">Baveno</a>. We recommend visiting the Borromean Islands, which are just a short boat ride away. There are also the botanical Gardens of Villa Taranto and lots of lovely walks straight from your hotel. Or, why not book onto one of our exclusive Inghams guided walks and get to know the hidden gems of the area. When you’re not out walking or sightseeing, explore the old town where bars and restaurants spill out onto cobbled squares, and enjoy leisurely strolls along the lakefront promenade.</p>
<p><a data-udi="umb://document/476c8caf3fe84faab565f2d0f2e99f48" href="/{localLink:umb://document/476c8caf3fe84faab565f2d0f2e99f48}" title="Lake Maggiore" class="c-btn c-btn--secondary c-btn c-btn--mid c-btn--secondary-hollow c-btn--wide u-text-center">Find Out More About Lake Maggiore</a></p>
<p><a href="tel:01483791111" class="InfinityNumber c-btn">Call Us to Book Today</a></p>]]></locationDescription>
